roposal: `changes/AR-038/proposal.md`\n66: - Spec: `changes/AR-038/spec.md`\n67: - Root Delta Spec: `delta-spec.md`\n68: - pkg/workloadmanager directory: `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n69: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) |\n| Module | pkg/workloadmanager |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Design | [Stage ST-0 pending] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Add task phases and checklist items]\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775897033614,"end":1775897033642}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897033645,"sessionID":"ses_2844a15b4ffeNWy8IzOlAqIIqm","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb6335a001JHS8hEXTk4Iz65","messageID":"msg_d7bb60e55001Kc0UAw1j0e5XQS","sessionID":"ses_2844a15b4ffeNWy8IzOlAqIIqm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9fd5d5da7fa2434f94f299f09e2343f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-038/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-038/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) |\n8: | Module | pkg/workloadmanager |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### Component Overview\n18: \n19: ```\n20: pkg/workloadmanager/\n21: ├── server.go           # HTTPServer - manages HTTP lifecycle, graceful shutdown\n22: ├── config.go           # Config - server configuration parameters\n23: ├── router.go           # Router - chi.Router wrapper for route registration\n24: ├── types.go            # Types - error types, response types, interfaces\n25: ├── store.go            # MemoryStore - in-memory sandbox storage with sync.RWMutex\n26: ├── lifecycle.go        # SandboxLifecycleManager - sandbox CRUD operations\n27: ├── garbage_collector.go # GarbageCollector - periodic cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes\n28: ├── k8s_client.go       # K8sClient - Kubernetes client wrapper with informer factory\n29: ├── informers.go        # Informers - informer lifecycle management\n30: ├── defaults.go         # Constants - default timeouts, GVRs, labels\n31: ├── handlers/\n32: │   ├── handler.go      # HandlerFunc, HandlerFuncAdapter\n33: │   ├── health.go       # HealthHandler - /healthz, /readyz endpoints\n34: │   └── sandbox_delete.go # DeletionHandler - DELETE /v1/*/sessions/{sessionId}\n35: └── middleware/\n36:     ├── logging.go      # LoggingMiddleware - request logging\n37:     ├── recovery.go     # RecoveryMiddleware - panic recovery\n38:     └── cors.go         # CORSMiddleware - CORS headers\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ### Data Flow Diagram\n42: \n43: ```\n44: HTTP Request → Middleware Chain → Router → Handler → LifecycleManager → Store/K8sClient\n45:                      ↓\n46:               Error Handling (HandleError)\n47:                      ↓\n48:               JSON Response (ErrorResponse/SuccessResponse)\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Component Interactions\n52: \n53: ```\n54: HTTPServer\n55:     │\n56:     ├── Router (chi.Router)\n57:     │       ├── HealthHandler (Register)\n58:     │       ├── DeletionHandler (Register)\n59:     │       └── Middleware Chain: Recovery → Logging → CORS\n60:     │\n61:     ├── GarbageCollector (background goroutine)\n62:     │       └── SandboxLifecycleManager\n63:     │               ├── Store (MemoryStore)\n64:     │               └── K8sClient (dynamic.Client)\n65:     │\n66:     └── Informers (cache sync for Pod informer)\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## Data Structures\n72: \n73: ### Core Types\n74: \n75: #### SandboxInfo (`pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`)\n76: ```go\n77: type SandboxInfo struct {\n78:     Kind               string              // AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Sandbox, SandboxClaim\n79:     SandboxID          string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n80:     SandboxNamespace   string              // Kubernetes namespace\n81:     SandboxName        string              // Kubernetes resource name\n82:     Name               string              // User-provided name\n83:     SessionID          string              // Session identifier (key for Store)\n84:     CreatedAt          time.Time           // Creation timestamp\n85:     ExpiresAt          time.Time           // Expiration timestamp\n86:     Status             string              // running, terminating, etc.\n87:     EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint // Access endpoints\n88:     UserToken          string              // User authentication token\n89:     ServiceAccount     string              // Service account name\n90:     ServiceAccountName string              // Service account name\n91:     LastActivity       time.Time           // Last activity timestamp (for idle timeout)\n92: }\n93: ```\n94: \n95: #### MemoryStore (`store.go`)\n96: ```go\n97: type MemoryStore struct {\n98:     mu              sync.RWMutex          // Read-write mutex for concurrent access\n99:     sandboxes       map[string]*types.SandboxInfo  // SessionID → SandboxInfo\n100:     expirationIndex map[string]time.Time           // SandboxID → ExpiresAt\n101: }\n102: ```\n103: \n104: #### HTTPServer (`server.go`)\n105: ```go\n106: type HTTPServer struct {\n107:     server           *http.Server\n108:     router           chi.Router\n109:     config           Config\n110:     handlers         map[string]Handler\n111:     logger           Logger\n112:     stopCh           chan struct{}\n113:     lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager\n114:     garbageCollector *GarbageCollector\n115:     store            Store\n116:     k8sClient        *K8sClient\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: #### GarbageCollector (`garbage_collector.go`)\n121: ```go\n122: type GarbageCollector struct {\n123:     manager     *SandboxLifecycleManager\n124:     interval    time.Duration\n125:     onceTimeout time.Duration\n126:     stopCh      chan struct{}\n127:     wg          sync.WaitGroup\n128:     logger      Logger\n129:     idleTimeout time.Duration\n130:     idleMu      sync.RWMutex\n131: }\n132: ```\n133: \n134: #### K8sClient (`k8s_client.go`)\n135: ```go\n136: type K8sClient struct {\n137:     dynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n138:     coreClient      kubernetes.Interface\n139:     informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n140:     podLister       corev1listers.PodLister\n141:     podInformer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n142:     scheme          *runtime.Scheme\n143: }\n144: ```\n145: \n146: #### ClientCache (`k8s_client.go`)\n147: ```go\n148: type ClientCache struct {\n149:     mu      sync.RWMutex\n150:     clients map[string]dynamic.Interface  // key: \"{token}-{namespace}\"\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Error Types (`types.go`)\n155: ```go\n156: type ErrorResponse struct {\n157:     Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n158:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n159:     Details any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n160: }\n161: \n162: type ValidationError struct { Field string; Reason string }\n163: type NotFoundError struct { Resource string; Name string }\n164: type InternalError struct { Err error }\n165: type ServiceUnavailableError struct { Dependency string }\n166: type ConflictError struct { Resource string; Err error }\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## API Contracts\n172: \n173: ### Store Interface\n174: ```go\n175: type Store interface {\n176:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n177:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n178:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n179:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n180:     ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n181:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n182:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ### Logger Interface\n187: ```go\n188: type Logger interface {\n189:     Info(msg string, args ...any)\n190:     Error(msg string, args ...any)\n191: }\n192: ```\n193: \n194: ### Handler Interface\n195: ```go\n196: type Handler interface {\n197:     Register(r chi.Router)\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ### HTTP Endpoints\n202: \n203: | Path | Method | Handler | Description |\n204: |------|--------|---------|-------------|\n205: | `/healthz` | GET | HealthHandler.healthz | Liveness probe |\n206: | `/readyz` | GET | HealthHandler.readyz | Readiness probe |\n207: | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}` | DELETE | DeletionHandler | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n208: | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}` | DELETE | DeletionHandler | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n209: \n210: ### HTTP Response Codes\n211: \n212: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Response Code |\n213: |------------|-------------|---------------|\n214: | ValidationError | 400 Bad Request | VALIDATION_ERROR |\n215: | NotFoundError | 404 Not Found | NOT_FOUND |\n216: | ServiceUnavailableError | 503 Service Unavailable | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE |\n217: | InternalError | 500 Internal Server Error | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n218: | ConflictError | 500 Internal Server Error | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n219: \n220: ---\n221: \n222: ## Error Handling\n223: \n224: ### Strategy\n225: \n226: 1. **Error Propagation**: Errors propagate from Store → LifecycleManager → Handler → HandleError\n227: 2. **Error Mapping**: Type switch in `HandleError()` maps Go errors to HTTP status codes\n228: 3. **Logging**: All errors logged via Logger interface before response\n229: 4. **Panic Recovery**: RecoveryMiddleware catches panics, logs, returns HTTP 500\n230: \n231: ### Error Flow\n232: ```\n233: Handler → manager.DeleteSandbox()\n234:     → store.GetSandboxBySessionID() → NotFoundError\n235:     → k8sClient.DynamicClient().Delete() → apierrors.IsNotFound, IsConflict\n236:     → handleDeleteError() → NotFoundError→nil, ConflictError→ConflictError, else→InternalError\n237:     → HandleError() → HTTP Response\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ### Test Error Scenarios\n241: \n242: | Scenario | Error Type | Expected Behavior |\n243: |----------|------------|-------------------|\n244: | Sandbox not found | NotFoundError | HTTP 404, continue deletion |\n245: | Kubernetes API conflict | ConflictError | HTTP 500, logged |\n246: | Kubernetes API timeout | InternalError | HTTP 500, logged |\n247: | Store internal error | InternalError | HTTP 500, logged |\n248: | Validation failure | ValidationError | HTTP 400 |\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## Testing Strategy\n253: \n254: ### Test Categories\n255: \n256: | Category | Files | Purpose |\n257: |----------|-------|---------|\n258: | Unit Tests | *_test.go | Test individual functions/methods |\n259: | Table-Driven Tests | store_test.go, types_test.go | Parameterized test cases |\n260: | Concurrent Tests | store_test.go, garbage_collector_test.go | Race detection, thread safety |\n261: | Integration Tests | integration_test.go | E2E HTTP server lifecycle |\n262: | Benchmark Tests | benchmark_test.go (new) | Performance baselines |\n263: \n264: ### Test Patterns\n265: \n266: #### 1. Table-Driven Tests (Recommended)\n267: ```go\n268: func TestMemoryStore_Operations(t *testing.T) {\n269:     tests := []struct {\n270:         name    string\n271:         setup   func(*MemoryStore)\n272:         action  func(*MemoryStore) error\n273:         wantErr bool\n274:         errType error\n275:     }{\n276:         {name: \"store_new_sandbox\", ...},\n277:         {name: \"store_duplicate_session\", ...},\n278:         {name: \"get_nonexistent\", ...},\n279:     }\n280:     for _, tt := range tests {\n281:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) { ... })\n282:     }\n283: }\n284: ```\n285: \n286: #### 2. Mock/Fake Pattern\n287: ```go\n288: type mockLogger struct {\n289:     mu         sync.Mutex\n290:     infoCalls  []string\n291:     errorCalls []string\n292: }\n293: \n294: func (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {\n295:     l.mu.Lock()\n296:     defer l.mu.Unlock()\n297:     l.infoCalls = append(l.infoCalls, msg)\n298: }\n299: ```\n300: \n301: #### 3. Fake Kubernetes Client\n302: ```go\n303: func setupTestK8sClient() *K8sClient {\n304:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n305:     dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n306:     informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n307:     return &K8sClient{\n308:         dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n309:         coreClient:      fakeClient,\n310:         informerFactory: informerFactory,\n311:     }\n312: }\n313: ```\n314: \n315: #### 4. Concurrent Test Pattern\n316: ```go\n317: func TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T) {\n318:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n319:     var wg sync.WaitGroup\n320:     \n321:     for i := 0; i < 100; i++ {\n322:         wg.Add(1)\n323:         go func(id int) {\n324:             defer wg.Done()\n325:             store.StoreSandbox(ctx, &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: fmt.Sprintf(\"session-%d\", id)})\n326:         }(i)\n327:     }\n328:     \n329:     wg.Wait()\n330:     assert.Equal(t, 100, store.Size())\n331: }\n332: ```\n333: \n334: ### Test Coverage Targets\n335: \n336: | Component | Current Coverage | Target Coverage |\n337: |-----------|------------------|-----------------|\n338: | MemoryStore | ~70% | ≥85% |\n339: | SandboxLifecycleManager | ~65% | ≥80% |\n340: | GarbageCollector | ~60% | ≥80% |\n341: | HTTPServer | ~50% | ≥75% |\n342: | Handlers | ~60% | ≥80% |\n343: | Middleware | ~70% | ≥85% |\n344: | Types/Error | ~90% | ≥95% |\n345: | **Overall** | ~65% | **≥80%** |\n346: \n347: ### Test Execution Commands\n348: \n349: ```bash\n350: # Run all tests with race detection\n351: go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n352: \n353: # Run with coverage\n354: go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n355: \n356: # Generate coverage report\n357: go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n358: go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n359: \n360: # Run short tests (skip slow tests)\n361: go test -short ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n362: \n363: # Run benchmarks\n364: go test -bench=. -benchmem ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n365: ```\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ## File Structure\n370: \n371: ### Existing Test Files\n372: \n373: | File | Lines | Test Count | Coverage Focus |\n374: |------|-------|------------|----------------|\n375: | store_test.go | 381 | 12 | MemoryStore CRUD, concurrent access |\n376: | lifecycle_test.go | 353 | 14 | LifecycleManager, deletion, expiration |\n377: | garbage_collector_test.go | 379 | 10 | GC loop, batch processing, concurrent |\n378: | server_test.go | 138 | 7 | HTTPServer initialization, routing |\n379: | types_test.go | 166 | 12 | Error types, HandleError |\n380: | k8s_client_test.go | 128 | 6 | K8sClient, ClientCache |\n381: | informers_test.go | - | - | Informer lifecycle |\n382: | config_test.go | - | - | Config defaults |\n383: | defaults_test.go | - | - | Constants validation |\n384: | router_test.go | - | - | Router registration |\n385: | handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go | 248 | 10 | DeletionHandler, response format |\n386: | handlers/health_test.go | - | - | Health endpoints |\n387: | handlers/handler_test.go | - | - | HandlerFunc adapter |\n388: | middleware/logging_test.go | 123 | 8 | LoggingMiddleware |\n389: | middleware/recovery_test.go | - | - | RecoveryMiddleware |\n390: | middleware/cors_test.go | - | - | CORSMiddleware |\n391: | integration_test.go | 313 | 6 | E2E server lifecycle |\n392: \n393: ### New Test Files to Create\n394: \n395: | File | Purpose |\n396: |------|---------|\n397: | benchmark_test.go | Performance baselines for MemoryStore, GC, LifecycleManager |\n398: | fakes/fake_store.go | Configurable Fake Store for complex test scenarios |\n399: | fakes/fake_k8s_client.go | Fake K8sClient with customizable behavior |\n400: | mocks/mock_store.go | testify/mock Store for expectations verification |\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Dependencies\n405: \n406: ### Go Dependencies\n407: \n408: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n409: |---------|---------|---------|\n410: | github.com/stretchr/testify | v1.9.0 | Assertions (assert, require), Mock framework |\n411: | github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 | v5.0.12 | HTTP routing framework |\n412: | k8s.io/client-go | v0.31.0 | Kubernetes client library |\n413: | k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake | v0.31.0 | Fake Kubernetes client |\n414: | k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake | v0.31.0 | Fake dynamic client |\n415: | k8s.io/apimachinery | v0.31.0 | API types, errors (apierrors) |\n416: | k8s.io/utils | v0.0.0-20240711033017-18e509b52bc8 | ptr.To() utility |\n417: \n418: ### Test-Specific Dependencies\n419: \n420: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n421: |---------|---------|---------|\n422: | testing (stdlib) | - | Go test framework |\n423: | net/http/httptest (stdlib) | - | HTTP test utilities |\n424: | encoding/json (stdlib) | - | JSON response verification |\n425: \n426: ---\n427: \n428: ## Implementation Notes\n429: \n430: ### 1. Benchmark Test Design\n431: \n432: ```go\n433: func BenchmarkMemoryStore_StoreSandbox(b *testing.B) {\n434:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n435:     sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n436:         SessionID: \"benchmark-session\",\n437:         ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n438:     }\n439:     \n440:     b.ResetTimer()\n441:     for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n442:         sandbox.SessionID = fmt.Sprintf(\"session-%d\", i)\n443:         store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n444:     }\n445: }\n446: \n447: func BenchmarkMemoryStore_ConcurrentRead(b *testing.B) {\n448:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n449:     // Pre-populate with 1000 sandboxes\n450:     \n451:     b.RunParallel(func(pb *testing.PB) {\n452:         for pb.Next() {\n453:             store.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-500\")\n454:         }\n455:     })\n456: }\n457: ```\n458: \n459: ### 2. Context Cancellation Tests\n460: \n461: ```go\n462: func TestSandboxLifecycleManager_DeleteSandbox_ContextCancellation(t *testing.T) {\n463:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n464:     cancel() // Cancel immediately\n465:     \n466:     err := manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, \"session-123\")\n467:     assert.Error(t, err) // Should handle cancelled context gracefully\n468: }\n469: ```\n470: \n471: ### 3. Timeout Tests\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContextTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n475:     gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, time.Minute, 1*time.Nanosecond, logger)\n476:     \n477:     // Create many sandboxes to exceed timeout\n478:     for i := 0; i < 1000; i++ {\n479:         store.StoreSandbox(ctx, expiredSandbox)\n480:     }\n481:     \n482:     err := gc.runOnce(context.Background())\n483:     // Should handle timeout gracefully, not panic\n484: }\n485: ```\n486: \n487: ### 4. Stop/Start Cycle Tests\n488: \n489: ```go\n490: func TestGarbageCollector_StopStartCycle(t *testing.T) {\n491:     gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, 100*time.Millisecond, 1*time.Second, logger)\n492:     \n493:     gc.Start()\n494:     time.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n495:     gc.Stop()\n496:     \n497:     // Should be able to start again\n498:     gc = NewGarbageCollector(manager, 100*time.Millisecond, 1*time.Second, logger)\n499:     gc.Start()\n500:     gc.Stop()\n501: }\n502: ```\n503: \n504: ### 5. ClientCache Race Tests\n505: \n506: ```go\n507: func TestClientCache_ConcurrentGetOrCreate(t *testing.T) {\n508:     cache := NewClientCache()\n509:     config := &rest.Config{Host: \"http://localhost\"}\n510:     \n511:     var wg sync.WaitGroup\n512:     for i := 0; i < 100; i++ {\n513:         wg.Add(1)\n514:         go func(id int) {\n515:             defer wg.Done()\n516:             client, _ := cache.GetOrCreateClient(\"token\", fmt.Sprintf(\"ns-%d\", id%10), config)\n517:             assert.NotNil(t, client)\n518:         }(i)\n519:     }\n520:     wg.Wait()\n521: }\n522: ```\n523: \n524: ### 6. Graceful Shutdown Tests\n525: \n526: ```go\n527: func TestHTTPServer_GracefulShutdown_SignalHandling(t *testing.T) {\n528:     s := NewHTTPServer(DefaultConfig(), logger)\n529:     s.Start()\n530:     \n531:     // Simulate SIGTERM\n532:     syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n533:     \n534:     time.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)\n535:     \n536:     // Verify server stopped gracefully\n537:     select {\n538:     case <-s.stopCh:\n539:         // Success\n540:     case <-time.After(1 * time.Second):\n541:         t.Error(\"server did not stop after SIGTERM\")\n542:     }\n543: }\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ## References\n549: \n550: - Spec: `changes/AR-038/spec.md`\n551: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-038/delta-spec.md`\n552: - Proposal: `changes/AR-038/proposal.md`\n553: - Tasks: `changes/AR-038/tasks.md`\n554: - pkg/workloadmanager directory: `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n555: - client-go library spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n556: - Kubernetes fake client documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\n557: - testify documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/stretchr/testify\n558: - Go testing best practices: https://go.dev/blog/table-driven-tests\n559: - chi router documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\n\n(End of file - total 559 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) |\n| Module | pkg/workloadmanager |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Overview\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-038/design.md","time":{"start":1775897033612,"end":1775897033643}}}}
